BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-stats 
BuildRequires:    R-nnet 
Requires:         R-stats 
Requires:         R-nnet 

%description
Adjusted odds ratio conditional on potential confounders can be directly
obtained from logistic regression. However, those adjusted odds ratios
have been widely incorrectly interpreted as a relative risk. As relative
risk is often of interest in public health, we provide a simple code to
return adjusted relative risks from logistic regression model under
potential confounders.

%prep
%setup -q -c -n %{packname}

find -type f -executable -exec grep -Iq . {} \; -exec sed -i -e '$a\' {} \;

